graphical and historical evidence, Constantine and the Captive Christians of Persia presents an evocative and evolving portrait of the first Christian emperor, uncovering how Syriac Christians manipulated the image of their western Christian counterparts to fashion their own political and religious identities during this century of radical change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 0aSyriac ChristiansxHistoryyTo 1500vSources. 0aSyriac ChristianszIranxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aSyriac ChristianszIraqxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aRELIGION / Ancient.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066754740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096420440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964204423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964204/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles